# Test Patterns and API Signatures

## Token Counter Test Patterns

When testing token counters and conversation summarizers, use these patterns:

### ModelConfig Setup

Always create a proper ModelConfig with API keys for testing:

```go
testConfig := &config.ModelConfig{
    AnthropicAPIKey: "dummy-key-for-testing",
    ConversationSummary: config.ConversationSummaryConfig{
        MaxTokens: 5000,
        SummaryTokens: 200,
        MinConversationsToSummarize: 3,
        ModelForSummary: "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
        TokenProvider: "openai", // or "anthropic" or "auto"
    },
}
```

### Factory and Counter Creation

```go
// Factory creation
factory := NewDefaultTokenCounterFactory(testConfig)

// Counter creation
counter, err := NewAnthropicTokenCounter("dummy-key-for-testing", "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022")

// Summarizer creation
summarizer, err := NewConversationSummarizer(g, testConfig)
```

### Genkit Setup Pattern

```go
ctx := context.Background()
logger := mylog.NewLogger("debug", "text")
g, err := genkit.NewGenkit(ctx, testConfig, logger, false)
require.NoError(t, err)
```

## ProcessConversationHistory Testing

Always pass both conversations and files separately:

```go
result, err := summarizer.ProcessConversationHistory(ctx, conversations, []File{})
```

## Import Requirements

Test files need these imports:

- `"github.com/habiliai/agentruntime/config"`
- `"github.com/habiliai/agentruntime/internal/genkit"`
- `"github.com/habiliai/agentruntime/internal/mylog"`
- `"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert"`
- `"github.com/stretchr/testify/require"`
